# CLAUDE.md, project-level instructions

> **This is a template** for the project-level `CLAUDE.md` file at the root of any project where you run Claude Code. Keep it under ~50 lines. Pointers, not content. Chris's actual CLAUDE.md follows this exact pattern (slide 28 + 45 of [chris-demo.html](https://chris1928a.github.io/eo-ai-exchange/events/01-2026-05-11-setup-trap/chris-demo.html)).

---

## Project context

I am [your name]. This project is [what the project is about].

My current quarter focus is in `memory/user_focus_q{N}_{YYYY}.md`.

## My hats / domains

I operate across N domains. Per-hat memory in `memory/hats/`:
- [hat-1] — see `memory/hats/<hat>.md`
- [hat-2] — see `memory/hats/<hat>.md`
- ...

## Voice rules

Strict voice rules in `memory/feedback_voice.md`. Banned words list and channel-specific tone there. **You are not allowed to use** any of: delve, leverage, harness, robust, seamless, em-dashes, "I hope this finds you well".

## Tools you can use

MCP servers loaded for this project:
- Gmail (read/send)
- Calendar (read/create)
- Notion (read/write to specific databases — see `memory/_meta/notion_scope.md`)
- [add yours]

## Hooks

- PreToolUse: confirm before any file write or destructive command
- PostToolUse: auto-commit memory changes to git

## Where things live (the routing)

- **Long-term memory:** GitHub repo `<your-repo-name>` + Notion (`memory/_meta/notion_index.md` lists which Notion pages are read vs write)
- **Short-term memory:** `memory/` directory in this project
- **Working memory:** wherever Claude Code is running (your machine or a VM)
- **Body / tools:** MCP servers above + cron jobs in `crons/` + Telegram bot

## Skills

Skills loaded from `~/.claude/skills/`. Per-project skill aliases in `memory/_meta/skill_aliases.md`.

## Cron jobs

Defined in `crons/`. Currently: morning-brief (07:00), weekly-review (Fri 17:00), memory-curator (Sun 14:00).

## Don't

- **Never** push to git without showing me the diff first
- **Never** invoke a destructive shell command without explicit confirmation
- **Never** write to Notion outside the scopes in `notion_scope.md`
- **Never** include personal data (names, emails, phone numbers) in any artifact destined for the public repo

---

## Length discipline

This file is intentionally short. **~50 lines max.** It's a router, not content. If you find yourself wanting to add more, ask: "Should this be a memory file instead?"

If yes, create `memory/<type>_<topic>.md` and add a one-line pointer here.
